# Bot (`apps/bot`)

## Env

`TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN`, `API_BASE_URL` (Express origin, no trailing slash), `BOT_INTERNAL_TOKEN` (must match server).

## Entry

`src/index.ts` — `registerVerifyCommand`, `registerStatusCommand`, `/start` (help text lists `/verify`, `/status`, `/upgrade`).

## API client (`services/apiClient.ts`)

- Headers: `x-internal-bot-token`, `x-telegram-user-id`, optional URI-encoded name headers.
- **`verifyNafdac`**, **`recordBotActivity`**, **`initializeBotProCheckout`**, **`fetchBotStatus`** (`POST /api/bot/status`).

## Commands

| Command | Module | Behavior |
|---------|--------|----------|
| `/start` | `index.ts` | Help + optional activity POST |
| `/verify` | `verifyCommand.ts` | Arg or pending text → `GET /api/verify/:nafdac` |
| `/upgrade` | `verifyCommand.ts` | `initializeBotProCheckout` → Paystack link |
| `/status` | `statusCommand.ts` | Plan, total + today usage, Pro period end |

## Copy

- Distinguish **“without Bot Pro”** vs **Bot Pro** — avoid lines that sound like everyone is on a single “free tier” when Pro users might read them.
- Daily limit replies and `/start` footer: point to **`/upgrade`** and **`/status`** for plan/usage.

## Conventions

ESM + **`.js` imports** in source; HTML replies only where content is controlled/escaped.

See **`9jacheckr-overview.mdc`** for full handbook.
